I"<<p>A quick little tip for mixing epoxy in the shop. Just stick some tape on the edge of your work bench, and make sure to leave a bit of a tag hanging off.</p>

<p><a href="/assets/ShopTricks/epoxytape.jpg"><img src="/assets/ShopTricks/Thumbnails/epoxytape.jpg" alt="Tape to mix on" /></a></p>

<p>I save most of my thin cutoffs for things like spacers, shims, inlays and mixing 2-part adhesives.</p>

<p><a href="/assets/ShopTricks/cutoffs.jpg"><img src="/assets/ShopTricks/Thumbnails/cutoffs.jpg" alt="Stuff to mix with" /></a></p>

<p>Easy, quick and little waste.</p>
